summary: This document is an email from the NYPD to the FBI, dated June 28, 2019, listing vehicle license plates associated with Jeffrey Epstein in Florida and New York. It is part of the NYPD/FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force investigation.

events.title: NYPD provides Epstein vehicle info to FBI
events.description: The NYPD sends an email to the FBI listing vehicle license plates associated with Jeffrey Epstein in Florida and New York as part of a child exploitation and human trafficking investigation.

keyFacts: The NYPD and FBI were actively collaborating on a Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force investigation into Jeffrey Epstein as of June 2019.
The investigation tracked specific vehicles associated with Epstein: two 2018-2019 black Chevy Suburbans in Florida and one 2016 black Chevy Suburban in New York.
The document is dated June 28, 2019, which is after Epstein's July 2019 arrest, indicating ongoing investigative activity.
